            3. Customers can still subscribe for new products with trial periods, in which case discounts won’t apply.
            4. Discount codes can be only applied if you’re not in trial period 
        * Solution
            * Discounts can be thought of as a generalization whereas trial subscriptions can be a specialization. 
            * Both of them have a start/end date (in case of discount it’ll be the remaining window). Both of them have to calculate cost differently for a the specified period. (In case of trials, this cost is 0.0)

